# RulesTools — PROJECT

## Identity

- **Name:** RulesTools
- **Package:** `rulestools` (GitHub)
- **Purpose:** Static code scanner + MCP servers — one binary, three modes
- **GitHub:** github.com/lpmwfx/RulesTools

## Current Stack

- Rust (clap, serde, ureq)
- Single binary: `rulestools` (CLI + MCP tools + MCP rules)

## Architecture

One binary replaces what was 3 separate executables:
- `rulestools scan/check/list/detect/setup/init/new/update/upgrade/publish/issue` — CLI
- `rulestools mcp-tools` — MCP server for scan, setup, init, publish (stdio)
- `rulestools mcp-rules` — MCP server for rule lookup, search (stdio)

MCP handlers call internal functions directly — no subprocess, no version drift.

## Constraints

- Must install from GitHub — never from local D: paths
- Output format (VSCode problem-matcher) must stay identical
- `proj/ISSUES` format is a contract — no breaking changes
- Pre-commit hook integration must work throughout
